[{"id":"VR786364","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows an insulating sphere concentric with and surrounded by a conducting shell. The shell is connected to ground by a wire. The radius of the sphere is 0.1 meter, the inner radius of the shell is 0.2 meter, and the outer radius of the shell is 0.25 meter.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR786364.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A charged insulating sphere is surrounded by a concentric, spherical conducting shell that is connected to ground, as shown in the figure. The insulating sphere has a radius of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.10 meter\"><math alttext=\"0.10 meter\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.10</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></span></span> and a symmetric charge density <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"rho of r, equals beta times r cubed\"><math alttext=\"rho of r, equals beta times r cubed\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mi>ρ</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>r</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>β</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>3</mn></msup></mstyle></math></span></span>, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r\"><math alttext=\"r\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> is the distance from the sphere’s center and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"beta\"><math alttext=\"beta\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>β</mi></math></span></span> is a constant equal to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"6.0 coulombs per meter to the sixth power\"><math alttext=\"6.0 coulombs per meter to the sixth power\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>6.0</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>/</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>6</mn></msup></math></span></span>. The conducting shell has an inner radius of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.20 meter\"><math alttext=\"0.20 meter\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.20</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></span></span> and an outer radius of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.25 meter\"><math alttext=\"0.25 meter\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>0.25</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math></span></span>. What is the charge on the inner surface of the conducting shell?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR786364_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Zero</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative 13 microcoulombs\"><math alttext=\"negative 13 microcoulombs\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>−</mo><mn>13</mn></mpadded><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>μC</mtext></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative 25 microcoulombs\"><math alttext=\"negative 25 microcoulombs\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>−</mo><mn>25</mn></mpadded><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>μC</mtext></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative 75 microcoulombs\"><math alttext=\"negative 75 microcoulombs\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>−</mo><mn>75</mn></mpadded><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>μC</mtext></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":1}]